LeetCode 724. Find Pivot Index

Problem
Find the index where:

sum of elements on left == sum of elements on right

Return the leftmost pivot index, else return -1.

1. Brute Force
Idea

For every index i:

compute left sum
compute right sum
compare
Time Complexity
O(n²)
Space Complexity
O(1)
Code
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            int leftSum = 0;
            int rightSum = 0;

            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
                leftSum += nums[j];
            }

            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; j++) {
                rightSum += nums[j];
            }

            if (leftSum == rightSum) {
                return i;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}

2. Prefix Sum Array (Better)
Idea

Build prefix array:

prefix[i] = sum of nums[0..i]

Then:

leftSum = prefix[i-1]
rightSum = prefix[n-1] - prefix[i]
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(n)
Code
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {

        int n = nums.length;
        int[] prefix = new int[n];

        prefix[0] = nums[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            prefix[i] = prefix[i - 1] + nums[i];
        }

        int total = prefix[n - 1];

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            int leftSum = (i == 0) ? 0 : prefix[i - 1];
            int rightSum = total - prefix[i];

            if (leftSum == rightSum) {
                return i;
            }
        }

        return -1;
    }
}

3. Optimal (Running Sum)
Idea (Most Important)

Instead of prefix array:

keep leftSum
compute rightSum using total sum
rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - nums[i]
Algorithm
Compute total sum
Traverse array
Check pivot condition
Update left sum
Time Complexity
O(n)
Space Complexity
O(1)
Code (Optimal)
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {

        int totalSum = 0;

        for (int num : nums) {
            totalSum += num;
        }

        int leftSum = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {

            int rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - nums[i];

            if (leftSum == rightSum) {
                return i;
            }

            leftSum += nums[i];
        }

        return -1;
    }
}

4. “Product-style Thinking” Variant (NOT ACTUAL PIVOT, BUT INTERVIEW INSIGHT)

Sometimes students try to apply:

product / nums[i]

This does NOT work for pivot index, because pivot is based on SUM, not PRODUCT.

But here is the correct “product-style analogy”:

Equivalent transformation idea

We use:

totalSum = leftSum + nums[i] + rightSum

So:

rightSum = totalSum - leftSum - nums[i]

This is the SUM equivalent of prefix/suffix logic used in product problems.

